<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1202">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.67/69</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Canada</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 891</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department encloses herewith a copy
                            of a letter dated April 21, 1916, from Mr. Cyrus Adler, of New York
                            City, relative to the reported persecution, at Vera Cruz, of Ottoman
                            subjects of the Jewish faith.</p>
                        <p>The Department desires you to exercise your unofficial good offices in
                            behalf of Ottoman subjects in your district, in accordance with the
                            instruction sent to you under date of January 9, 1915.<note n="2" xml:id="d1202fn2">
                                <ref target="frus1915#pg_1072">For. Rel. 1915, p. 1072</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>